==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Consopite
<hw>Con"so*pite</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To lull to sleep; to quiet;
to compose.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The operation of the masculine faculties of the soul were, for a
while, well slacked and <qex>consopited</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Dr. H.
More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consort</ent>⟦br⟧
